    "MOA_summary": "Single-cell regulatory network analysis identifies state-specific master regulator programs in IDH mutant glioma; high-throughput drug screening (OncoTreat) predicts compounds that invert these programs (e.g., cisplatin for AC-like, DS\u2011651b for NPC-like, micofenolate for OC-like), enabling rational combination strategies validated in patient-derived slice explants.",
    "readouts": [
      "single-nucleus RNA-seq",
      "Viper activity inference",
      "OncoTreat drug ranking",
      "ex vivo slice drug response"
    ],
    "key_findings": [
      "Three conserved malignant cell states (AC-like, NPC-like, OC-like) were defined across oligodendroglioma and astrocytoma with distinct master regulator programs.",
      "OncoTreat identified state-specific drug vulnerabilities: DNA damage repair inhibitors for AC-like, MAPK pathway inhibitors for NPC-like, and purine synthesis inhibitors for OC-like.",
      "Preliminary ex vivo slice experiments suggest serum biomarkers can detect early state shifts, supporting translational potential."
    ],
    "novelty_flag": "platform_technology",
